For a long time, the Electric Imp was my favorite IoT-enabler. I have even
taught a few workshops on how to use it. The Imp is an ARM Cortex M3 processor,
running at 3.3V, and it includes wireless connectivity (802.11 b/g/n) using the
same chip you will find in an iPhone. The breakout board from SparkFun
[https://www.sparkfun.com/products/12886] will give you hookups for battery and
USB power, and six (6) GPIO pins.

