Java guy at heart, and still very much enjoy a good old fashioned JAR to deploy
into my project - and that is exactly what Autobahn provides. You will first
need to download that library, and add it to your Android project.

private final WebSocketConnection   socket = new WebSocketConnection();

...

try {
  socket.connect(BLUEMIX, new WebSocketHandler() {
    @Override
    public void onOpen() {
      // Debug
      Log.d("WEBSOCKETS", "Connected to server.");
    }

    @Override
    public void onTextMessage(String payload) {
      // Debug
      Log.d("WEBSOCKETS", payload);
    }

    @Override
    public void onClose(int code, String reason) {
      // Debug
      Log.d("WEBSOCKETS", "Connection lost.");
    }
  });
} catch(WebSocketException wse) {
  Log.d("WEBSOCKETS", wse.getMessage());
}


The declaration of the WebSocket client is declared "final" to avoid memory
